A lot of this hill is covered in
trees and other vegetation,

00:02:08.400 --> 00:02:11.840
and they will help anchor the sand
and keep everything in place.

00:02:11.840 --> 00:02:13.040
So I had to ask:

00:02:13.040 --> 00:02:15.440
surely all the people
descending this mountain

00:02:15.440 --> 00:02:17.600
keep dragging the sand down with them?

00:02:47.280 --> 00:02:49.920
I'm sure that the local government
could have insisted

00:02:49.920 --> 00:02:53.040
that this hill be cleaned up and
the sand disposed of somehow.

00:02:53.040 --> 00:02:57.200
But why would they? Now, Hirschau
isn't just a mining town.

00:02:57.200 --> 00:02:59.600
It's a mining town with a
local theme park.

00:02:59.600 --> 00:03:01.680
Tourists have a reason to come here,
and spend money.

00:03:01.680 --> 00:03:03.360
There are more jobs for the locals.

00:03:03.360 --> 00:03:07.360
And every so often, someone will come along
and tell the world that, hey,

00:03:07.360 --> 00:03:10.640
there's a ski slope made of sand in Germany.

